\f1  May 29, 1929.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1 On this day, Peter Ware Higgs (1929-) is born. He is an English theoretical {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://hepweb.rl.ac.uk/ppUKpics/POW/pr_000105.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}}, the namesake of the Higgs boson. In the late 1960s, Higgs and others proposed a mechanism that would endow particles with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cern.ch/Public/SCIENCE/massmystery.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mass}}, even though they appeared originally in a theory - and possibly in the Universe! - with no mass at all. The basic idea is that all particles acquire their mass through interactions with an all-pervading field, called the 
\f2\i Higgs field
\f1\i0 . which is carried by the 
\f2\i Higgs bosons
\f1\i0 . This {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://atlasinfo.cern.ch/Atlas/documentation/EDUC/physics10.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mechanism}} is an important part of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www2.slac.stanford.edu/vvc/theory/model.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Standard Model}} of particles and forces, for it explains the masses of the carriers of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://hepweb.rl.ac.uk/ppUKpics/POW/pr_990113.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 weak force}}, responsible for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://durpdg.dur.ac.uk/lbl/cpep/npe.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 beta-decay}} and for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://gamma.nrl.navy.mil/dap-aps/dapaps/posters/Neu/neu_revised.jpg"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 nuclear reactions}} that fuel the Sun.  
\f3\fs28 \cf5 \cb6 On 4 July 2012, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CERN"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 CERN}} announced the discovery of the boson at the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Large_Hadron_Collider"}}{\fldrslt \cf7 Large Hadron Collider}} and the subsequent year Peter Higgs was awarded with the Nobel Prize in Physics.\
\
